Where to build bike station based on distance to closest station and population?


Grid elements containing a bike station are filtered out, and for remaining squares an arbitrary index is calculated. Index is calculated by population of square divided by distance from center of square to closest bike station.
This yields a greater value for high population squares far away from an existing bike station. The index is normalized by autoscaling and values below zero are filtered out. This means squares with a better situation (=low pop and close to station) are filtered out, as zero represents mean after autoscale.
